job.title: IIT Hyderabad System Engineer Recruitment 2021  Apply Online for Various  Vacancies in Hyderabad
job.body:
Total Vacancies: various.

Name of the Vacancies:

  • Network/System Engineer

Description

New Hyderabad Government Jobs have been published by IIT Hyderabad for the Vacancies of System Engineer in Hyderabad. If you are finding a government job in Hyderabad then it is an opportunity for you. You can fill the online application for these vacancies in Hyderabad, from 24.04.2021, and till 15.05.2021. If you are interested in all these vacancies in Hyderabad and if eligible, please check out the details given below, which have been given age limit, educational qualification pay scale, etc.


Application fee

  • Mode of application is Online

Educational qualification to apply for IIT System Engineer posts in Hyderabad:

  • To apply for a System Engineer post in Hyderabad, your B.Tech/B.E, B.Sc, M.Sc, MCA must be completed from a recognized University

Important dates

  • The starting date to apply in these posts is the 24.04.2021
  •  Last date to apply in these posts is 15.05.2021

Age Limit Criteria

  • For General Candidate, you should be between 21 Years. to 37  years old. 

IIT System Engineer Pay Scale

  • According to the information given by the Hyderabad Government and as per the 7th pay commission, the teacher's monthly salary is 20,000 to 30,000.

How to apply for IIT Hyderabad System Engineer Recruitment 2021?

Press the Apply Now button above. You can directly and easily start the application process for these vacancies in Hyderabad. Fill in your details and submit it

Or follow all the steps given below,

  •  First, go to the official website of IIT Hyderabad and register yourself on the portal.
  • Find the notification, log in and then provide the details and documents asked BY IIT Hyderabad.
  • Then save it and complete the application submission.
  • Then to fully complete the process you have to submit the application fee.
  • And finally, download the application form for future purposes.
